channel.title: Help! please
channel.description: WTF is wrong with my god damn router. i got an amazing server coded and i wanna host it so bad, but no my piece of shit cant see my port 43594.... i know for a fucking fact i portforwarded right. I even got uTorrent portforward for me.. but newazhawha it cant find fucking 43594. can someone help to see whats wrong. no im not downloading team viewer.. im on my work laptop :)

item.title: Help! please
item.dc:creator: @demps2k9 demps2k9
item.description:
@demps2k9 wrote:

I wouldn’t consider using UTorrent. Re-check your router and also check that you allowed the ports correctly through your firewall.

If non of those 2 work download No-Ip if you don’t have it asit is needed. And make sure you have the correct server ip added in your clients gui.java or client.java.
